4 HJR___ RECOGNIZING FEBRUARY 10, 2026, AS ALPHA PHI ALPHA DAY
5 AT THE ALABAMA STATE CAPITOL.
6
7 WHEREAS, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Incorporated,
8 the first intercollegiate Greek-letter fraternity
9 established for African Americans, was founded at Cornell
10 University in Ithaca, New York, on December 4, 1906, by
11 Henry Arthur Callis, Charles Henry Chapman, Eugene Kinckle
12 Jones, George Biddle Kelley, Nathaniel Allison Murray,
13 Robert Harold Ogle, and Vertner Woodson Tandy, known as the
14 "Jewels"; who recognized the need for a strong bond of
15 brotherhood among African descendants in this country; and
16 WHEREAS, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Incorporated,
17 for 119 years has been a beacon of light to the community by
18 standing true to its aims of manly deeds, scholarship, and
19 love for all mankind; and
20 WHEREAS, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Incorporated,
21 has produced over 200,000 members that were inducted into
22 706 college and alumni chapters in the United States,
23 Europe, Asia, and the Caribbean; and
24 WHEREAS, Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Incorporated,
25 continues to make a difference in our society through the
26 fraternity's national programs of civic outreach initiatives
27 which accumulate over one million hours of community
28 service, producing $2.5 million in scholarships, and has
Page 1

service, producing $2.5 million in scholarships, and has
HJR100 INTRODUCED
29 registering thousands of American citizens to participate in
30 the voting process; and
31 WHEREAS, the 18th Annual "Alpha Day at the Capitol"
32 convenes under the leadership of Alabama District Director
33 Michael Raynard Mayberry and District Deputy Director Kelvin
34 T. Wallace, Sr., representing 32 chapters across the State
35 of Alabama; now therefore,
36 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
37 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That the members of this body
38 commend Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Incorporated, and the
39 Alabama District Chapters for their outstanding
40 contributions to this nation and the State of Alabama and
41 recognize February 10, 2026, as Alpha Phi Alpha Day at the
42 Alabama State Capitol.
